{"word":"παραχρῆμα","slug":"παραχρῆμα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>παραχρῆμα</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:παρά\">παρά</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:χρῆμα\">χρῆμα</a></el> ‘thing for use’] <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ adv.\">adv.</a> <b>instantly, immediately</b> (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> our ‘on the spot’) <b><a href='B:470 21:19'>Mt 21:19f</a>; <a href='B:490 1:64'>Lk 1:64</a></b> and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ oft.\">oft.</a> in Lk and Acts, but in <b><a href='B:490 19:11'>Lk 19:11</a> soon</b> expresses the nuance conveyed by <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:μέλλω\">μέλλω</a></el> in the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pres.\">pres.</a> tense, in contrast to the secondary tenses in all other passages. <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:παραχράομαι\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:πάρδαλις\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}